![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

The **Multichannel Distribution settings **tab allows you to generate the [Multichannel Distribution configuration file](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/MD%2BDelivery%2BChannel%2BOption%2BFile%2B%28LOTXML%29%2BSpecification) (**LOTXML**), which allows to manage all LOTXML elements.

**Option**

**Description**

**Generate the Multichannel Distribution configuration file**

Enables/disables the generation of the Multichannel Distribution configuration file.

**External id**

The *externalId *element of the LOTXML file; it is the batch identification for the application that produced it.

**File name**

Name of the generated LOTXML file.

**Bom Id**

The *bomId *element of the LOTXML file, used to identify the BOM.

**Environment Dn**

The *environmentDn *field of the LOTXML file: environment.

**Path**

Path of the generated LOTXML file.

**Use case**

The *useCase *field of the LOTXML file: use case.

- **BATCH **

- **ONDEMAND **

- **PROOFING**

**Priority**

The *priority *field of the LOTXML file: priorities of the lot, applied to all messages contained in it.

**Gateways**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Enables/disables type of gateways

Select a gateway to start its configuration

## **Gateways configuration**
### Email &amp; PEC
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Email or PEC SMTP Gateway configuration:

**Option**

**Description**

**Codepage**

Encoding used to encode the body and send the message:

- **UTF-8**

- **ISO-8859-1**

**Subject**

Post subject

**From**

Sender address

**Name**

Sender name

**Reply to**

Reply to address

**Name Reply to**

Reply to name

**Username**

Server authentication info: username

**Password**

Server authentication info: password

**Message Id**

Message identifier

**Addresses**

Recipient addresses:

- **Type: **Recipient type

- **TO **

- **CC **

- **BCC**

**Address**: Email address

**Name: **Recipient's name

**Priority**

Message priority:

- **Lowest **

- **Low **

- **Normal **

- **High **

- **Highest**

**Attachments**

Files to attach:

- **Type**

**Embedded **

- **Hyperlink**

- **Path (For both Embedded and Hyperlink): **Absolute path of the physical file source

- **PlaceHolder (For Hyperlink): **Placeholder in the body representing the URL of the referenced file. It must be unique within the list of files.

**X-Headers**

One row for each header to insert in the email:

- **Name**: name of the key (with "X-"), the name must be all uppercase and omit the ":" that the system automatically enters.

- **Value: **value of the x-header, omitting the ":" that the system automatically enters.

### Fax
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Fax Gateway configuration:

**Description**

**Parameter**

**Destination**

International phone number

**Content path**

Path to the file that contains the text of the Fax to be sent.

**Sender**

Sender

**Quality**

Faxing resolution:

- **Medium **

- **Low**

### Fileshare
![](data:image/png;base64,)

File transfer Gateway configuration:

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Message Remote sub path**

Remote subfolder name where the files will be transferred. The path is relative to the root configured on the gateway and will be created if necessary.

**Files**

Group of files to be sent:

- **Path**: path of the file on the local system.

- **File Remote sub path**: path of the file on the remote server.

> Note

For more information, see: How to Define a Remote Subpath for Each File, Overriding the Default Setting

### Remote Fileshare
![](data:image/png;base64,)

FTP Gateway configuration:

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Message Remote sub path**

Name of the remote subfolder where the files will be transferred. The path is relative to the root configured on the gateway and will be created if necessary.

**Files**

Group of files to be sent:

- **Path**: path of the file relative to that of the lot

- **File Remote sub path**: path of the file on the remote server relative to the login folder.

> Note

For more information, see: How to Define a Remote Subpath for Each File, Overriding the Default Setting
